graph TD
    subgraph User Interaction
        A[User Query] -- "Ask a question" --> B(Query Pre-processing:
        - Rephrasing, Intent Detection)
    end

    subgraph Retrieval Phase
        B --> C(Embed Query:
        - Vectorize User Query)
        C --> D{Vector Search / Retrieval:
        - Find Top-K similar chunks}
        D -- "Retrieved Chunks" --> E(Context Formulation:
        - Assemble relevant info for LLM)
    end

    subgraph Generation Phase
        E -- "Prompt + Context" --> F[Large Language Model (LLM):
        - Generate Answer]
        F -- "Raw Answer" --> G(Response Post-processing:
        - Formatting, Filtering, Safety)
        G --> H[Final Answer to User]
    end

    subgraph Knowledge Base / CRM Documentation Sources
        direction LR
        KBA[Knowledge Base Articles:
        - FAQs, How-to Guides]
        CRM_Cases[CRM Cases & Notes:
        - Support Tickets, Sales Notes]
        ProdDocs[Product Documentation:
        - Manuals, Specs, Release Notes]
        SupportLogs[Support Chat/Call Logs:
        - Transcripts, Resolutions]
        ExternalDocs[External Vendor Docs:
        - Partner Guides, APIs]

        KBA & CRM_Cases & ProdDocs & SupportLogs & ExternalDocs -- "Cleaned, Chunked, Embedded" --> I[Vector Database / Index:
        - Stores vector embeddings of docs]
    end

    I -- "Similar Embeddings" --> D

    subgraph Documentation Quality Factors
        DQ_CRITERIA[Documentation Quality Criteria:
        - **Accuracy:** Factual correctness
        - **Completeness:** Full information
        - **Consistency:** Uniform terminology/data
        - **Timeliness:** Up-to-date info
        - **Structure & Tagging:** Organized, searchable
        - **Relevance:** Pertinent to user needs]

        style DQ_CRITERIA fill:#E0FFFF,stroke:#20B2AA,stroke-width:2px,color:#333
    end

    subgraph Impact of Doc Quality on RAG
        DQ_CRITERIA -- "High Quality Docs Lead To" --> I
        DQ_CRITERIA -- "Low Quality Docs Lead To:" --> LowQ_Impact_Retrieval[Impact on Retrieval:
        - Irrelevant/Outdated Chunks
        - Poor Embedding Quality
        - Missed Information]
        DQ_CRITERIA -- "Low Quality Docs Lead To:" --> LowQ_Impact_Generation[Impact on Generation:
        - Misleading/Conflicting Context
        - Hallucinations/Inaccurate Answers
        - Suboptimal/Vague User Experience]

        I -- "Ensures good search" --> D
        LowQ_Impact_Retrieval -- "Bad Input for Search" --> D
        LowQ_Impact_Retrieval -- "Poor Context" --> E

        E -- "Ensures good prompt" --> F
        LowQ_Impact_Generation -- "Bad Context for LLM" --> F
        LowQ_Impact_Generation -- "Poor Output Quality" --> H

        style LowQ_Impact_Retrieval fill:#FFDDC2,stroke:#FF8C00,stroke-width:2px,color:#333
        style LowQ_Impact_Generation fill:#FFDDC2,stroke:#FF8C00,stroke-width:2px,color:#333
    end

    subgraph Feedback & Continuous Improvement
        H -- "User Feedback (Rating, Correction, "Was this helpful?")" --> J[Human Review & Content Update:
        - Subject Matter Experts, Content Editors]
        J --> KBA
        J --> CRM_Cases
        J --> ProdDocs
        J --> SupportLogs
        J -. "Improves Documentation Quality" .-> DQ_CRITERIA
        style J fill:#D3F4EE,stroke:#1ABC9C,stroke-width:2px,color:#333
    end